Workflow 

We often say slow is smooth, smooth is fast. This works well for longer tedious tasks, such as ropesetting commercial flow and stripping a zone, but does not fully capture many of the efficiencies to make our job both physically and mentally easier. An efficient setter has their systems dialed to suit their personal needs and style in consideration of their crew. An inefficient setter wastes precious energy repeating unnecessary tasks, going back and forth, and overworking their body more than necessary.  

 

It’s important to note the difference between moving efficiently and moving fast. Moving fast can be costly; not only to the product offering’s quality but also to the safety of the setters and community. We must not conflate the two. Skipping screw checks, leaving a dirty zone, and rushing the strip are NOT efficient; they are amateur ways of trying to move faster. 

 

